quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  28,29,"Then when Moses had completed the term and set out with his family, he perceived a fire on the side of the Mount. He said to his family, “Stay here. I perceive a fire. Perhaps I will bring you some news therefrom, or a firebrand, that haply you may warm yourselves.”"
  28,30,"And when he came upon it, he was called from the right bank of the valley, at the blessed site, from the tree, “O Moses! Truly I am God, Lord of the worlds!”"
  28,31,"and, “Cast thy staff!” Then when he saw it quivering like a serpent, he turned in retreat without returning. “O Moses! Approach and fear not! Truly, thou art of those who are secure"
  28,32,"Insert thy hand in thy bosom; it will come forth white, without blemish. And draw thine arms to thyself against fear. These are two proofs from thy Lord to Pharaoh and his notables. Verily they are an iniquitous people.”"
  28,33,"He said, “My Lord! Verily I have killed a soul among them, and I fear that they will slay me"
  28,34,"And my brother, Aaron, is more eloquent than me in speech. So send him with me as a helper to confirm me, for I fear they will deny me.”"
  28,35,"He said, “We shall strengthen thine arm through thy brother, and We shall grant an authority for both of you, such that they shall not reach you. With Our signs, you and those who follow you shall be the victors.”"
  28,36,"But when Moses brought them Our clear signs, they said, “This is naught but fabricated sorcery. We heard this not among our fathers of old.”"
  28,37,"Moses said, “My Lord knows best who brings guidance from Him, and whose end is the Abode. Truly the wrongdoers will not prosper.”"
  28,38,"Pharaoh said, “O notables! I know of no god for you other than myself. So kindle for me a fire, O Haman, for clay, and make me a tower, that haply I may behold the God of Moses, though truly I think he is among the liars.”"
  28,39,"And he and his hosts waxed arrogant upon the earth, without right, and they thought they would not be returned unto Us"
  28,40,"So We seized him and his hosts, and cast them into the sea. So behold how the wrongdoers fared in the end"
  28,41,And We made them imams calling unto the Fire. And on the Day of Resurrection they will not be helped
  28,42,And We caused them to be pursued by a curse in this world. And on the Day of Resurrection they will be among the repugnant
  28,43,"And indeed We gave unto Moses the Book—after We had destroyed the former generations—as a [source of] insight for mankind, and guidance and mercy, that haply they may reflect"
  28,44,"And thou wast not on the western side when We decreed unto Moses the Commandment, and thou wast not among the witnesses"
  28,45,"But it is We Who brought into being the generations, and lives grew long for them. And thou dwelt not among the people of Midian, reciting unto them Our signs. But it is We Who sent"
  28,46,"And thou wast not on the side of the Mount when We called out. But [thou art sent as] a mercy from thy Lord that thou mayest warn a people unto whom no warner has come before thee, that haply they may remember"
  28,47,"And [We did so] lest there be an affliction that would befall them because of that which their hands have sent forth at which they should say, “Our Lord! If only Thou hadst sent a messenger unto us, we would have followed Thy signs and been among the believers!”"
  28,48,"But when the truth came to them from Us, they said, “Why was he not given the like of that which was given to Moses?” Did they not disbelieve in that which was given to Moses aforetime? They said, “Two sorceries, supporting one another.” And they said, “Truly we are disbelievers in each.”"
  28,49,"Say, “So bring a book from God that provides better guidance than these two, that I may follow it, if you are truthful.”"
  28,50,"And if they respond not to thee, then know that they follow only their caprices. And who is more astray than one who follows his caprice without guidance from God? Surely God guides not wrongdoing people"